# Why: Documenso PAdES-signs every sealed PDF (CAdES/PKCS#7 +
#      optional TSA, see packages/signing/) and appends a Signing
#      Certificate page. In Adobe Acrobat Reader this triggers a blue
#      "Signed and all signatures are valid" banner — strong legal
#      provenance. But ~95% of merchants open contract PDFs in Chrome,
#      Mac Preview, or mobile viewers that DON'T validate PAdES, so
#      they never see that banner. The document feels less authoritative
#      than it actually is.
#
#      This patch stamps a small Dotloop-style footer at the bottom of
#      every contract-body page (NOT certificate / audit-log pages —
#      those have their own provenance markings). Format:
#
#        Verified by sign.pacta.ink · Envelope <id> · Signed <ts> UTC
#
#      Footer is muted gray (gray-500), 6.5pt Noto Sans, centered at
#      14pt from page bottom. Survives single-page screenshots and is
#      visible regardless of PDF viewer. Skipped for rejected
#      documents (those carry a different visual stamp via
#      addRejectionStampToPdf).
#
# Why-not-additive: The footer-drawing function itself IS additive —
#      it lives at packages/bizrethink/server-only/pdf/add-verification-footer-to-pdf.ts.
#      But seal-document.handler.ts (the upstream sealer) has to import
#      and call it. That import + call is what this patch adds.
#
# Upstream-merge-fragility: LOW
#      Single new import + one if-block insertion before the certificate
#      copy. DecorateAndSignPdfOptions extended with `completedAt`
#      (single new key in a Pick — doesn't shift positional behavior).
#
# Files patched:
#   - packages/lib/jobs/definitions/internal/seal-document.handler.ts
#
# Files added (no patch):
#   - packages/bizrethink/server-only/pdf/add-verification-footer-to-pdf.ts

